On Tue, 25 Oct 2005, Andy wrote:

> Hmmm... By nature and definition, dielectrics are electrically
> non-conductive. They may coat and prevent corrosion on certain metals,
> but they also electrically insulate.

True, but in a battery terminal the connection is metal-to-metal.  The
pressure of clamping will push the grease out of the connection  This
action is desirable, as it plugs the microscopic passaged that allow
corrosion-promoting substances into the terminal.
